{Welcome to one of the most fearsome openings - the dreaded Halloween Gambit! A 
gambit so vile that no Grandmaster has yet dared to try it by the light of a 
serious OTB event, but make no mistake - in the depths of the internet it has 
been known to snare many an unwary denizen. So let's begin - if you dare!} 1. e4 
e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 {Suspecting nothing...} 4. Nxe5 $5 {Gasp! Clearly our 
opponent is a complete lunatic. Or possibly Simon Williams. Or both!} Nxe5 {This 
guide will hopefully provide you the means to confront the madness before us in 
a variety of ways. But before we proceed any further, a warning: do not 
underestimate the depths of the depravity of White's devilish designs! Many an 
unsuspecting player has defended superficially against this attack, thinking it 
too ludicrous to be taken seriously, and found out to their ruin the cost of 
their indifference. In fact, the more I examine this opening I'm often tempted 
to play this as White in the (very reasonable) hope that my opponents haven't 
read this guide. In any event, prepare ye, defenders of chess righteousness, for 
the chaos that you shall soon face. Good luck and Godspeed!} *

